      "span_text": "The patient lies in supine position while the practitioner holds his wrist and slowly and gradually lifts it to an overhead position with the arm externally rotated. The arm of the patient is then abducted while traction is applied, initiating reduction. If the reduction does not occur, the practitioner can internally rotate the arm and press on the humeral head. [CITATION_1] "
